:: StudentAssign2 {"position":"425,350","size":"100,100"}
(if: $role is not "student")[
(set: $role to "student")
(set: $time to 72)
(set: $exhaustion to 2)

It's 11:41 PM, Thursday. You've got three assignments due Monday: a Stats problem set, a lab report for your ML class, and a 1,500-word essay for COMP380 on algorithmic governance and democratic consent.

You work a 7 AM shift at the library Friday morning. Your roommate Kenzie is on her bed with her laptop open, using ChatGPT Plus to draft her own COMP380 essay. She's offered, twice, to show you her workflow.

The syllabus says AI use is "strictly prohibited" and will be "referred to the Office of Academic Integrity without exception." The syllabus also says all essays will be screened by ''OriginalCheck''.

You sit down with the essay prompt open in one tab. In another tab, a ChatGPT login page is waiting.

(link: "Start the Stats problem set first. You think better in the morning.")[
(set: $time to it - 5)
(set: $studentAction to "econ-first")
(go-to: "StudentAssign2")
]

(link: "Open ChatGPT. You can always not paste anything.")[
(set: $time to it - 4)
(set: $studentAction to "opened-chat")
(go-to: "StudentAssign2")
]
]
(else:)[
(if: $studentAction is "econ-first")[You grind through the Stats set. It takes five hours. You finish at 4:30 AM. You sleep for two hours. You go to your library shift. You come home at 1 PM, sleep for another two, and start the COMP380 essay at 3:15.]
(else-if: $studentAction is "opened-chat")[You open ChatGPT and stare at the cursor. You type: "can you explain what algorithmic governance means, in plain language, without writing anything I could submit." It answers in two paragraphs. The answer is begrudgingly useful. You take notes and close the tab. You tell yourself you're not cheating because the AI is not actually writing it for you, then you do the Stats set by hand.]

It's Saturday afternoon. You start the COMP380 essay.

The prompt is: //"Is algorithmic governance compatible with democratic consent?"//

You write for two hours and end up with 600 words. They aren't good 600 words.

Kenzie pokes her head in. //"I got my grade back already. A minus. The AI thing flagged 0%."// She genuinely doesn't think she did anything wrong.

You stare at your 600 words.

(link: "Close ChatGPT. Write the rest yourself. Sleep less.")[
(set: $exhaustion to it + 3)
(set: $time to it - 12)
(set: $grade1 to "honest")
(go-to: "StudentAssign3")
]

(link: "Use ChatGPT to draft a skeleton. Rewrite every sentence in your own voice.")[
(set: $aiUsage to it + 1)
(set: $exhaustion to it + 1)
(set: $time to it - 5)
(set: $grade1 to "hybrid")
(go-to: "StudentAssign3")
]

(link: "Paste the prompt. Have it write the whole thing. Edit lightly.")[
(set: $aiUsage to it + 2)
(set: $time to it - 2)
(set: $grade1 to "all-ai")
(go-to: "StudentAssign3")
]
]


:: StudentAssign3 {"position":"550,350","size":"100,100"}
(if: $grade1 is "honest")[You close the tab and write from 4 PM to 2 AM, stopping only for ramen and a phone call from your sister that you cut short. At 2:17 AM, you finish with 1,480 words. When you reread it, the essay feels honest, even if it is not the strongest one in the class. It says what you actually think.]
(else-if: $grade1 is "hybrid")[You paste the prompt into ChatGPT and ask for an outline, then a skeleton, then a few sample topic sentences. You rewrite every line, cutting anything that sounds too much like the model, and add the story your grandmother told you last Thanksgiving about the rebate check she was denied. By midnight, the essay is finished at 1,520 words. Some of it feels like yours, and some of it does not, but the line between the two has become harder to see.]
(else-if: $grade1 is "all-ai")[The essay takes twenty-seven minutes. You paste the prompt. You ask for 1,500 words. You ask it to "sound like a smart undergraduate." You read it and it's better than what you would've written, honestly. You change a few sentences. You swap "furthermore" for "also" in three places. 1,510 words. None of them yours. You've got most of the evening left. You watch a movie with Kenzie.]

Sunday afternoon. The ML lab report is 8 pages of data analysis and a 500-word discussion.

(if: $aiUsage >= 2)[You draft the discussion in ChatGPT in four minutes. You run it through a paraphraser twice. You tell yourself this is the last time you will be using AI.
(set: $aiUsage to it + 1)
(set: $time to it - 2)
]
(else:)[You write the discussion yourself and it takes three hours.
(set: $exhaustion to it + 1)
(set: $time to it - 4)
]

You submit all three assignments through the portal by 11:47 PM Sunday. An auto-reply: //"All essays will be screened by OriginalCheck within 48 hours."//

